'''Daisy Jazz Isobel Ridley''' (born 10 April 1992) is an English actress. Born in [[Westminster]] and brought up in [[Maida Vale]], Ridley trained in drama at the [[Tring Park School for the Performing Arts]]. She began acting in minor guest roles on television and in short films, making her film debut in the independent horror film [[Scrawl (film)|''Scrawl'']] (2015). 

Ridley rose to international prominence for playing the lead role of [[Rey (Star Wars)|Rey]] in the [[Star Wars sequel trilogy|''Star Wars'' sequel trilogy]], starring in ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'' (2015), ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]'' (2017), and the upcoming ''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker]]'' (2019). She has also appeared in the mystery film ''[[Murder on the Orient Express (2017 film)|Murder on the Orient Express]]'' (2017) and provided her voice to the animated film [[Peter Rabbit (film)|''Peter Rabbit'']] (2018).

==Early life==
Daisy Ridley was born on 10 April 1992 in [[Westminster]], London, and grew up in [[Maida Vale]].<ref name="fashionstyle">{{cite news|first1=Jess|last1=Goodwin|work=Fashion & Style|title=Daisy Ridley: 7 Things You Might Not Know About The 'Star Wars: Episode VII: The Force Awakens' Actress|url=http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/39630/20150107/daisy-ridley-7-things-you-might-not-know-about-the-star-wars-force-awakens-actress.htm|archive-url=https://archive.is/20150119002843/http://www.fashionnstyle.com/articles/39630/20150107/daisy-ridley-7-things-you-might-not-know-about-the-star-wars-force-awakens-actress.htm|dead-url=yes|archive-date=19 January 2015|date=7 January 2015|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Daisy Jazz I Ridley|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:QV41-GJ7S|publisher=[[FamilySearch]]|accessdate=21 October 2015}}</ref> She is the youngest of three daughters born to Louise Fawkner-Corbett, a banker, and Christopher Ridley, a photographer.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/film/2015112428417/all-you-need-to-know-about-daisy-ridley/|title=All you need to know about Daisy Ridley|date=25 November 2015|magazine=[[Hello! (magazine)|Hello!]]}}</ref> She has two older sisters, Kika Rose and Poppy Sophia.<ref>[http://www.etonline.com/news/175936_9_things_you_need_to_know_about_daisy_ridley/ "9 Things You Need to Know About 'Star Wars: The Force Awakens' Leading Lady Daisy Ridley"]. ''Entertainment Online''. "The London native's full name is Daisy Jazz Isobel Ridley. As if that wasn't magical enough, her siblings also have names fit for English roses -- one quite literally. Her two older sisters are Kika-Rose and Poppy Sophia, a model and aspiring musician, respectively. Ridley grew up in an exclusive community in central London, and her great-grandfather, William Victor Fawkner-Corbett, served as a colonel in World War I."</ref><ref>[http://heavy.com/entertainment/2014/04/daisy-ridley-star-wars-episode-7-cast/ "Daisy Ridley: Top 10 Facts You Need to Know"]. Heavy Entertainment. Retrieved 19 December 2015</ref> Her mother's family, the Fawkner-Corbetts, were [[landed gentry]] with a military and medical background.<ref>Burke's Landed Gentry 1952, pg 528, 'Fawkner-Corbett of Brown Edge'</ref> Her great-uncle was ''[[Dad's Army]]'' actor and playwright [[Arnold Ridley]]; his brother, Daisy's grandfather, John Harry Dunn Ridley, [[O.B.E.]], was head of the Engineering Secretariat at the [[BBC|B.B.C.]] from 1950 to 1965.<ref>Wireless World, vol. 71, I.P.C. Business Press Ltd, 1965, p. 232</ref><ref>B.B.C. Handbook, British Broadcasting Corporation, 1964, p. 167</ref><ref>The London Gazette, Supplement to the London Gazette, 1st January 1962, p. 19</ref><ref>Electronic Technology, vol. 39, Great Britain Radio Research Board, Iliffe and Sons Ltd, 1962, p. 81</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Breznican|first1=Anthony|title=Star Wars: The Force Awakens: As Rey emerges, so does newcomer Daisy Ridley|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/04/24/star-wars-force-awakens-rey-emerges-shadows-so-does-newcomer-daisy-ridley|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=26 April 2015|date=25 April 2015}}</ref> While growing up, her favourite film was ''[[Matilda (1996 film)|Matilda]]'' (1996), an adaptation of [[Roald Dahl]]'s [[Matilda (novel)|children's story]], with the [[Matilda Wormwood|title character]] (played by [[Mara Wilson]] in the film) a role model to her.<ref>{{cite news|title=Everything You Need to Know About Star Wars's New Stars John Boyega and Daisy Ridley|url=http://www.vogue.com/13380722/star-wars-john-boyega-daisy-ridley/|publisher=Vogue|date=20 May 2016}}</ref> Ridley won a scholarship to [[Tring Park School for the Performing Arts]] in [[Hertfordshire]], which she attended between the ages of 9 and 18.<ref name="mirror140501"/><ref name="TheSundayTimes151213"/> She then began reading classical civilisation at [[Birkbeck, University of London]], before dropping out to concentrate on her acting career.<ref name="TheSundayTimes151213">{{cite web|last1=Glass|first1=Katie|title=A new hope|url=http://failover-www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/style/living/article1642376.html|website=[[The Sunday Times]]|accessdate=10 January 2016|date=13 December 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160126030920/http://failover-www.thesundaytimes.co.uk/style/living/article1642376.html|archivedate=26 January 2016}}</ref> Prior to being cast in ''[[The Force Awakens]]'', Ridley worked as a [[bartender|barmaid]] in two different pubs in London for nearly two years.<ref name="VIP">{{cite web|last1=Foran|first1=Niamh|title=Daisy Ridley tells hilarious story of pulling pints in Dingle at Star Wars wrap party|url=http://vipmagazine.ie/daisy-ridley-tells-hilarious-story-of-pulling-pints-in-dingle-at-star-wars-wrap-party/|website=[[VIP (magazine)|VIP]]|accessdate=26 December 2017|date=1 December 2017}}</ref> In 2016 Ridley began studying for a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in [[social science]] through online courses with the [[Open University]].<ref name="Stylist">{{cite web|last1=Bownass|first1=Helen|title=Daisy Ridley on finding fame, Star Wars and her love for washing powder|url=https://www.stylist.co.uk/people/daisy-ridley-interview-star-wars-2017-issue-396-fame-washing-powder-london/179086|website=[[Stylist (magazine)|Stylist]]|accessdate=26 December 2017|date=12 December 2017}}</ref><ref name="HollywoodReporter">{{cite web|last1=Siegel|first1=Tatiana|title=Next Gen 2015: How Unknown Daisy Ridley's "Weird Feeling" Helped Her Land 'Star Wars' Role|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/next-gen-2015-how-unknown-836637|website=[[HollywoodReporter.com]]|accessdate=26 December 2017|date=4 November 2015}}</ref>

==Career==
===2013–2015: Early roles and ''Star Wars'' breakthrough===
Ridley began her career with minor roles in the television programmes ''[[Youngers]]'', ''[[Toast of London]]'', ''[[Silent Witness]]'', ''[[Mr Selfridge]]'', and ''[[Casualty (TV series)|Casualty]]''.<ref name="heavy140429"/><ref name="huff140429"/><ref name="mtv140429"/><ref name="newsok140504"/> She appeared in the short film ''Blue Season'', which was entered into the [[Sci-Fi-London]] 48-Hour Film Challenge.<ref name="huffpo140430"/> Ridley played the lead in film three of ''Lifesaver'',<ref name="lifesaver"/> an interactive film which was nominated for a [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts|BAFTA Award]].<ref name="bafta13"/> She also appeared in the music video for [[Wiley (rapper)|Wiley]]'s song "[[Lights On (Wiley song)|Lights On]]", playing the character of Kim.<ref name="mirror140501"/><ref name="elinf140429"/> Ridley made her film debut in the 2015 British independent horror film ''[[Scrawl (film)|Scrawl]]'', after her scenes from the British comedy film ''[[The Inbetweeners 2]]'' were removed in the final cut.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/star-wars-7s-daisy-ridley-cut-inbetweeners-2-1459295/|title=Star Wars 7's Daisy Ridley cut from Invetweeners 2|last=Skipper|first=Ben|date=1 August 2014|work=[[International Business Times]]}}</ref>

[[File:Women at NASA-nov4-2016.webm|thumb|Daisy Ridley and producer [[Kathleen Kennedy (producer)|Kathleen Kennedy]] discuss women who work for [[NASA]] in 2016.]]
In April 2014, Ridley's casting as Rey, one of the lead characters in ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'', was announced.<ref name="heavy140429" /><ref name="huff140429" /><ref name="mtv140429" /> She was chosen for the film in February 2014.<ref name="hollyrep140430" /> At the time of her casting she was, according to ''[[Rolling Stone]]'', a "total unknown."<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/features/star-wars-strikes-back-behind-the-scenes-of-the-biggest-movie-of-the-year-20151202 |work=Rolling Stone | title='Star Wars' Strikes Back: Behind the Scenes of the Biggest Movie of the Year | date=2 December 2015 | accessdate=11 December 2015 |author=Brian Hiatt}}</ref> Her choice by director [[J. J. Abrams]] was seen as a repeat of [[George Lucas]]'s move of casting relatively unknown actors for the lead roles in [[Star Wars (film)|the first ''Star Wars'' film]] in 1977.<ref name="dlyex140330" /> Ridley began filming her scenes in May 2014 at [[Pinewood Studios]] in [[Buckinghamshire]], and prior to the film's release in December 2015, she appeared at the launch of a set of ''Star Wars'' postage stamps issued by the UK postal service [[Royal Mail]], with her character Rey featuring on a stamp along with the droid [[BB-8]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-26639322|title=Episode VII filming to begin in UK in May|publisher=BBC News|date=18 March 2014|accessdate=18 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Star Wars stamps issued to mark The Force Awakens|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34620723|publisher=BBC|date=24 October 2015}}</ref> With international revenues of over $2&nbsp;billion,<ref name="BOM">{{cite web |title=Star Wars: The Force Awakens (2015)|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=starwars7.htm |publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=20 February 2016}}</ref> ''The Force Awakens'' was a major box-office hit and the [[2015 in film#Highest-grossing films|highest-grossing film of 2015]]. After an early screening of the film, Brian Viner of the ''[[Daily Mail]]'' called Ridley the "real star of the show", adding that her performance as Rey should "send her career into orbit."<ref>{{cite news|title=Star Wars: The Force Awakens gets rave reviews|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-35109900|publisher=BBC|date=16 December 2015}}</ref> Her performance received critical acclaim, with [[Richard Roeper]] describing her portrayal as "a breakout performance" and adding "Ford has a terrific father figure chemistry [shared] with Ridley and [[John Boyega|[John] Boyega]]".<ref>{{cite web |last=Roeper |first=Richard |date=16 December 2015 |title='Star Wars: The Force Awakens’': Thrills are strong with this one |work=Chicago Sun Times |url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/star-wars-the-force-awakens-review-the-thrills-are-strong-with-this-one/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160512204514/http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/star-wars-the-force-awakens-review-the-thrills-are-strong-with-this-one/ |archivedate=12 May 2016 |deadurl=no}}</ref>

===2016–present: After ''The Force Awakens''===
Ridley became executive producer of the documentary ''[[The Eagle Huntress]]'' in January 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Daisy Ridley Signs on as Exec Producer of The Eagle Huntress |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2016/01/25/daisy-ridley-signs-on-as-exec-producer-of-the-eagle-huntress |website=IGN |accessdate=25 January 2016}}</ref> Director Otto Bell said of her commitment, "Like so many other theatergoers around the world, I was blown away by Daisy's recent portrayal of an empowered female protagonist. I'm thrilled she'll be bringing that same energy to supporting a real-world heroine who is also on an epic journey to win victory in a far away land." The movie premiered at the [[Sundance Film Festival]] on 24 January 2016, with Ridley narrating.<ref>{{cite web|title='Star Wars' Daisy Ridley Becomes 'Eagle Huntress' Executive Producer |url=http://deadline.com/2016/01/star-wars-the-force-awakens-daisy-ridley-the-eagle-huntress-sundance-film-festival-1201687900/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=21 January 2016}}</ref> She was one of several actors featured on [[Barbra Streisand]]'s 2016 album ''[[Encore: Movie Partners Sing Broadway]]''. Along with [[Anne Hathaway]], Ridley and Streisand perform the song "[[At the Ballet]]" from ''[[A Chorus Line]]'', with Ridley performing the role of Bebe, one of a trio of dancers hoping to be cast in an upcoming show.<ref name=NPRAlbum>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/2016/08/18/490258191/first-listen-barbra-streisand-encore|title= Review: Barbra Streisand, 'Encore'|first= Mark|last= Mobley|date= 18 August 2016|work=npr.org |accessdate= 27 August 2016}}</ref><ref>Lowe, Lindsay, [https://parade.com/624740/lindsaylowe/daisy-ridley-on-having-tea-and-singing-at-barbra-streisands-house-i-literally-sobbed/ Daisy Ridley on Having Tea and Singing at Barbra Streisand’s House: ‘I Literally Sobbed’], [[Parade (magazine)|Parade]] 29 November 2017. Retrieved 11 December 2017.</ref>

In 2017, Ridley portrayed Mary Debenham in ''[[Murder on the Orient Express (2017 film)|Murder on the Orient Express]]'', an adaptation of [[Agatha Christie]]'s detective novel of the same name. Directed by and starring [[Kenneth Branagh]], production began in London in November 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=Daisy Ridley and Dame Judi Dench on board for Murder on the Orient Expres |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-37523752|agency=BBC News|date=30 September 2016}}</ref> She also reprised her role as Rey, opposite [[Mark Hamill]] as [[Luke Skywalker]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/star-wars-producer-kathleen-kennedy-confirms-that-entire-cast-will-return-for-eighth-film-a3139911.html|title=Star Wars producer Kathleen Kennedy confirms that entire cast will return for eighth film |last=Ruby|first=Jennifer|work=London Evening Standard|date=17 December 2015|accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref> in ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]'', which was released in December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/star-wars-episode-viii-gets-857601|title='Star Wars: Episode VIII' Gets New Release|first=Pamela|last=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=20 January 2016|accessdate=4 February 2016}}</ref>

In January 2018, Ridley starred in the titular role in ''[[Ophelia (2018 film)|Ophelia]]'', a reimagining of the [[Hamlet]] tale, alongside [[Naomi Watts]] and [[Clive Owen]]. The project was filmed from April to July 2017 and debuted at the [[2018 Sundance Film Festival]].<ref name="May2017CS">{{cite news|title=Daisy Ridley Photo from Ophelia - ComingSoon.net|url=http://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/850909-first-daisy-ridley-photo-from-ophelia#/slide/1|accessdate=23 May 2017|work=ComingSoon.net|date=22 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2017/11/2018-sundance-film-festival-lineup-jane-fonda-idris-elba-competition-movies-list-1202216273/|title=Sundance 2018: Jane Fonda Doc, Idris Elba, Election 2016, Gloria Allred & Oscar Wilde Films Among U.S., World Cinema, NEXT, Midnight & Kids Slates|first=Dominic|last=Patten|date=29 November 2017|publisher=}}</ref> In February 2018, Ridley voiced the role of Cottontail in ''[[Peter Rabbit (film)|Peter Rabbit]]'', an adaptation of the children's stories of the same name by [[Beatrix Potter]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Doty|first=Meriah|title=Daisy Ridley, Elizabeth Debicki Join 'Peter Rabbit' Live-Action/Animated Hybrid (Exclusive) |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/daisy-ridley-elizabeth-debicki-peter-rabbit-1201869183/|publisher=Variety|accessdate=25 October 2016|date=26 September 2016}}</ref>

====Upcoming roles====

In March 2019, Ridley will co-star in the ''[[Chaos Walking (film)|Chaos Walking]]'', an adaptation of the young adult novel by [[Patrick Ness]], as Viola Eade opposite [[Tom Holland (actor)|Tom Holland]] as Todd Hewitt. The project was filmed from August to November 2017.<ref>{{cite web |title=Daisy Ridley is moving to a world with no women in 'Chaos Rising' |url=http://mashable.com/2016/08/04/daisy-ridley-chaos-walking-lionsgate/ |website=Mashable.com |accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Marc |first=Christopher |url=http://omegaunderground.com/2017/07/30/confirmed-doug-limans-chaos-walking-begins-shooting-august-montreal/ |title=CONFIRMED: Doug Liman's 'Chaos Walking' Begins Shooting This August In Montreal |publisher=Omega Underground |date=30 July 2017 |accessdate=17 November 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170814035517/http://omegaunderground.com/2017/07/30/confirmed-doug-limans-chaos-walking-begins-shooting-august-montreal/ |archive-date=14 August 2017 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> In December 2019, Ridley will reprise her role as Rey in ''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker]]'', the last film in the sequel trilogy, filming in the summer of 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/jj-abrams-replace-colin-trevorrow-as-star-wars-episode-ix-writer-director-1037933?|title=J.J. Abrams to Replace Colin Trevorrow as 'Star Wars: Episode IX' Writer and Director|last=Parker|first=Ryan|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=12 September 2017|accessdate=10 October 2017}}</ref> She won't reprise Rey any more after this film.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://etcanada.com/news/469775/daisy-ridley-wont-reprise-rey-after-star-wars-rise-of-skywalker/ |title=Daisy Ridley Won’t Reprise Rey After ‘Star Wars: Rise Of Skywalker’ |first=Brent |last=Furdyk |date=29 June 2019 |access-date=5 July 2019 |work=[[ET Canada]] |publisher=[[Corus Entertainment Inc.]]}}</ref>

Also in 2018, Ridley will film ''Daddio'', a film that follows a woman who is picked up by a cab at JFK airport and driven to her apartment in Manhattan. On the way there, the woman and cabdriver begin discussing their past and current relationships and the effects those relationships have had on their lives.<ref>{{cite web|author=Justin Kroll |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/daisy-ridley-daddio-star-wars-1202575546/ |title=Daisy Ridley to Star in Drama ‘Daddio’ (EXCLUSIVE) – Variety |publisher=Variety.com |date=3 October 2017 |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref> Additionally, Ridley will reteam with director [[J. J. Abrams]] for ''Kolma'', which Abrams will also produce, a supernatural drama that finds a young woman who has suffered from a car crash that killed her boyfriend. When she dies decades later, she is given the choice of returning to the day of the accident to live her life again or being reunited with her love.<ref name="variety1">{{cite web|author=Justin Kroll |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/daisy-ridley-the-lost-wife-star-wars-1201760992/ |title=‘Star Wars’ Actress Daisy Ridley to Star in Drama ‘The Lost Wife’ (EXCLUSIVE) – Variety |publisher=Variety.com |date=26 April 2016 |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref> Ridley will star in ''The Lost Wife'' as Lanka, a Polish art student who has a love affair with her best friend's older brother that is torn apart by the German invasion during the onset of World War II.<ref name="variety1"/> Ridley has also signed on to star in ''A Woman of No Importance'', another Abrams-produced biographical political-thriller film based on Sonia Purnell's book of the same name. Ridley will portray American heiress and super-spy [[Virginia Hall]], who attempted to break into the ranks of the American Foreign Service in the years before World War II.<ref>{{cite web|author=Justin Kroll |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/daisy-ridley-a-woman-of-no-importance-paramount-1201968755/ |title=Daisy Ridley to Star in Spy Movie ‘A Woman of No Importance’ for Paramount – Variety |publisher=Variety.com |date=24 January 2017 |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref> Ridley will reteam with actor [[Josh Gad]] in the superhero-comedy ''Super-Normal'', to be released by [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kit|first=Borys|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/netflix-nabs-josh-gad-superhero-comedy-super-normal-1051758|title=Netflix Nabs Josh Gad Superhero Comedy 'Super-Normal' (Exclusive) |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=16 November 2017 |accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref> Ridley will also star in ''Piece of Mind''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/daisy-ridley-ryan-knighton-piece-of-mind-bad-robot-paramount-1202383022/|title=Ryan Knighton Adapting ‘Piece Of Mind’ For Daisy Ridley At Paramount & Bad Robot|first=Anthony D'Alessandro,Amanda|last=N'Duka|date=4 May 2018|publisher=}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Ridley has a tattoo of three stars on her left foot that she got when she was 15,<ref>{{cite web |title=Daisy Ridley tattoo stars foot - Daisy Ridley Star Wars The Force Awakens fun facts |url=http://www.wonderwall.com/celebrity/profiles/daisy-ridley-star-wars-the-force-awakens-10-things-to-know-fun-facts-34105.gallery?photoId=181576 |website=Wonderwall.com |accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref> a tattoo of the alchemical symbol of air on her right hip,<ref>{{cite web |title=Star Wars Daisy Ridley's Cute Tattoos |url=https://www.tattoodo.com/a/2016/01/star-wars-daisy-ridley-s-cute-tattoos/ |website=Tattoodo.com |accessdate=15 January 2016}}</ref> and a [[peace symbol]] tattoo behind her right ear.<ref>{{cite web |title=Daisy Ridley as Rey - Part 1 - Page 9 - The SuperHeroHype Forums |url=http://forums.superherohype.com/showthread.php?t=505915&page=9 |website=forums.superherohype.com |accessdate=12 March 2015}}</ref> As of April 2016, Ridley has a dog named Muffin.<ref>{{cite web |title=Daisy Ridley dog - Daisy Ridley Star Wars The Force Awakens fun facts |url=http://www.wonderwall.com/celebrity/profiles/daisy-ridley-star-wars-the-force-awakens-10-things-to-know-fun-facts-34105.gallery?photoId=181623 |website=Wonderwall.com |accessdate=7 April 2016}}</ref> Ridley supports [[Premier League]] football club [[Arsenal F.C.]]<ref>{{Citation|last=Vogue|title=73 Questions With Daisy Ridley {{!}} Vogue|date=11 October 2017|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=doUdRCrK80E&t=3m56s|accessdate=12 October 2017}}</ref> Ridley has appeared in ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine's World's Most Beautiful 2016 list.<ref>{{cite web |title=World's Most Beautiful 2016: Get Daisy Ridley's 5 Best Beauty Tips : People.com |url=http://www.people.com/people/package/article/0,,20998070_21001502,00.html |website=People.com |accessdate=22 April 2016}}</ref> Her rise to stardom saw Ridley appear on [[Debrett's]] 2016 list of the most influential people in the UK.<ref>{{cite news|title=Debrett's 500 List: Film|url=https://www.debretts.com/debretts-500-2016/list/|publisher=Debretts|date=21 May 2017}}</ref>

Ridley suffers from [[endometriosis]] and [[polycystic ovaries]], which required her to undergo multiple [[laparoscopic surgeries]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Daisy Ridley opened up about her struggle with endometriosis |url=http://www.cosmopolitan.co.uk/entertainment/news/a43962/daisy-ridley-opened-up-about-her-struggle-with-endomitriosis/ |website=Cosmopolitan |accessdate=12 June 2016}}</ref> She said on [[Instagram]] that she was diagnosed with the condition at the age of 15, and said it caused [[acne]] that lowered her [[self-esteem]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Daisy Ridley Opens Up About Her Struggles With Polycystic Ovary Syndrome And Endometriosis on Instagram |url=http://www.thefrisky.com/2016-06-13/daisy-ridley-opens-up-about-her-struggles-with-polycystic-ovary-syndrome-and-endometriosis-on-instagram/ |website=The Frisky |accessdate=13 June 2016}}</ref>

In August 2016, after receiving criticism for posting an [[Gun violence|anti-gun violence]] message on her Instagram account, Ridley deleted her Instagram account.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/style/2016/08/daisy-ridley-quits-instagram |title=Daisy Ridley Deletes Instagram Account over Post About Gun Violence |last=Bryant |first=Kenzie |website=Vanity Fair |access-date=20 August 2016}}</ref> The actress briefly returned to Instagram and said that the reason behind the deletion was because she had "a busy few months ahead and [so] wanted less distractions."<ref>{{cite web| title=Why has 'Star Wars' actress Daisy Ridley's Instagram account been deactivated? |url=http://mashable.com/2016/08/04/daisy-ridley-quitting-instagram/#Wpa.L9_ub5qd |website=Mashable.com |accessdate=20 August 2016}}</ref>

Ridley is in a relationship with actor [[Tom Bateman (actor)|Tom Bateman]]. In June 2019, Ridley announced that they were engaged.{{citation needed|date=July 2019}}

